args:
The prince's group joins with Yoshitsune,
head of the Rooster Wyrmclan, and begins an
operation to recapture the Halidom. However,
after separating from Seimei, they find
themselves lost in a mysterious barrier—and
in the confusion, Yoshitsune suddenly attacks!
Yes. Your spirits seemed down,\nand I thought this might help.
Well, thank you! I suppose I WAS feeling\na little low, what with my thoughts\nturned to the captured Halidom.
Heck, no worries there—I'd be fit to be\ntied if some weirdo busted into my barn\nand got up to the devil's mischief!
It's been a few days now. Do you think\nSeimei's barrier is still intact?

A'yup—though only just, I reckon.
If Doman decides to have at it tomorrow,
he'll likely bust it wide and send Yomi chi
floodin' out all over the place.
Still, Lord Seimei and the prince are\nbumpin' heads to come up with a plan,\nso I'm sure we'll all be juuust peachy.
Well, well. If it isn't Kuzunoha.
You most certainly do. Good to see\nyou're looking cheerful as ever.
Hot sweet potatoes! I can't believe\nya came all the way out here!
Where the Mukuroshu go, I follow.
This here's Lady Yoshitsune, leader of the\nRooster Wyrmclan! Her mission's to pursue\nthe Mukuroshu just like Lord Seimei.
Seimei sent word via shikigami. \nIt sounds like you all met with disaster.
Still, if hunting the Mukuroshu is your\nplan, you'll find me a more-than-capable\nally.

Right, here's the plan: We're going to start
our advance so we can retake the Halidom.
Seimei and Gozu Tenno will go first and
proceed straight to the castle.
Meanwhile, we'll take a more roundabout\npath that's less affected by the Yomi chi.
Uh, not to question your divine wisdom or\nnothing, but shouldn't we ALL take the\nsafe path? I mean, since it's there and all.

I realize your tiny body houses an equally
tiny brain, so I will be blunt: I must go
ahead and prepare the barrier so you
people are able to sneak through it.
Toootally coulda done that\nwithout the snark, dude.
Ha! Well, regardless, it seems we'll be\nseeing the two of you later.
Good. We're finally rid of the idiots,\nand have most of the information\nwe need about the castle to boot.
And now you and I will settle this,\njust as we planned from the beginning.
I have been preparing for this since\nthe day we first forged our soulpact.
Still, are we truly not going to tell\nKuzunoha? This will be our end, after all.
Obviously not. If we told her the truth,\nthat idiot would just raise a fuss.
That Seimei's got a tongue sharp enough\nto cut steel! He always like that?
Aw, don't be so hard on him. Lord Seimei's\ngot his charms—er, in his own way.
Your fondness for a man who continuously\nrefers to you as a fool is rather baffling.
Well sure, it hurts when he pokes fun,\nbut I really do respect him—not to\nmention I owe him m'darn life.

Well I used to just be an ordinary fox, but
folks were scared'a me 'cause I have lots
of spiritual energy. One day, somebody
took that fear and just up'n tried to kill me.

But Lord Seimei rescued me! He went
and shared his mana with me and turned
me into a shikigami—a sorta magical
conjured spirit, I guess ya'd say.
Makin' a shikigami takes a wagonload of\ntime'n effort, but he did it anyways.

He tried to brush it off by sayin' it beat
watchin' me die in front of him, but I
could tell he actually cared. So that's
how I know he ain't as bad as all that.
Which is why you follow him around now.
A'yup! Plus, I'm pretty helpful—his mouth\ngets him into heaps'a trouble, so I do\nmost'a the talkin' for him.
Yeah, you can't exactly call him the most\napproachable guy. Least not without you\nand Gozu Tenno around.
You know it! Still, he's been EXTRA\ncranky with y'all, even for him.
Probably 'cause this ain't just some\nordinary mission for him.
No? I thought he took this mission on\nbecause he didn't like the idea of doing\nthe usual fortune-spreading one.
Aw, that was just him puttin' on an act\nwhat for you folks. Findin' and defeatin'\nDoman is actually his life's work.
The two of 'em did seem to share\nsome kind of deeper connection,\nnow that you mention it.

Sure as shootin'! See, Doman used to
belong to the Bureau of Onmyodo, same
as Lord Seimei. Oh, that's basically the
head office for all onmyoji-related stuff.
But Doman betrayed the shogunate\nand hopped the fence to the Mukuroshu.
He got himself some fell onmyodo and\nused it to kill everyone in the Bureau—\neveryone 'cept Lord Seimei, that is.
A single man murderd all those people?\nIs Doman truly that powerful?
Heard rumors he used some sorta\nspecial curse to do it, but that stuff's\nway over this ol' fox's head.
But here's the kicker—one'a the onmyoji\nhe killed was Lord Seimei's grandfather.
That's why he's hoppin' mad at Doman—\nand why he'll move heck and breakfast\njust to have his revenge.
Hey, real quick—was this path\nALWAYS this long?
Good point. I thought we'd be in sight of\nthe Halidom by now, but the scenery\ndoesn't seem to have changed at all.
Folks in Hinomoto often get led astray by\nmischievous foxes. Y'all get that sorta\nthing here, or... Aw, heck!
It's a barrier! They hid the entrance\nso well I didn't even notice it!
Aw, boo! But hey, can't you just undo it\nwith your onmyodo whatever?
Not this fox. I don't got the skills what to\ntake down barriers when I don't know\nhow they got put up.

We didn't notice entering it, and there's
no way out... This here's one o' them
barriers what makes you lost no matter
which way ya wander.
And I assume Doman's the one\nresponsible for this barrier?
Reckon so. Likely hopin' to slow us down.
Then we've fallen into his trap?!
Now THIS is a fascinating trick.
However, if you don't wish to die here,\nI suggest you do as I will and fight\nwith absolutely everything you have.
Ahh, but it has been a while\nsince I fought in this form!
Okay, what the what is happening\nright now?! Why is she young?!

That there's Lady Yoshitsune's secret
technique! She uses it to turn her body
back to how it was when she was at her
most strong'n powerful.
What are you so afraid of? No matter what\nhappens on the battlefield, you must\nsimply face the foe standing before you.
So then...which of you would like your\nskull parted from your shoulders first?
What the heck's happened to ya,\nLady Yoshitsune?!
Didja betray the shogunate like Doman?!\nDidja really sink that low?!
Heh heh... And what if I have?
Ya didn't... I can't believe this,\nLady Yoshitsune!
We're out of options here, Kuzunoha.\nLet's fight her and stop her, and then we\ncan try to figure out what happened.
Well in that case, I'm gonna give 'er\neverything I got! Here goes nothin'!
